FBIS4-33122 "drlat106_p_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-106 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 Ecuador Roundup of Economic Developments Roundup of Economic Developments PA0106041894 PA0106041894 BFN [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of reports on economic developments monitored through 31 May. Augusto de la Torre, the director of the Central Bank of Ecuador, has described the tentative agreement reached with foreign banks to renegotiate the country's foreign commercial debt as "positive." De la Torre said he hopes other banks will soon express their support for this agreement. (Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 26 May 94) Monetary policy chief Ana Lucia Armijo has said that in June, the Ecuadoran Government will renegotiate its debt with the Paris Club. (Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 27 May 94)
